What the contract does:
The contract is securing a password
The vulnerability:
A private variable declared directly inside the contract can't be viewed by another contract but it can be used by anyone viewing the nodes ir web3 functions.
How I exploited it:
I knew that variable _password is stored in slot 1, and address of the instance so I used
await web3.eth.getStorageAt("0x67E874C280602e3F2219133B59fA0f64d53997aB", 1)
to get the password.
Prevention:
Any secret info shouldn't be stored inside a private variable. It should always be stored with the help of commit reveal schemes or zero knowledge proofs.
